Directions


                                            In a shallow bowl, whisk egg and milk. In another shallow bowl, combine the onions, cheese, bread crumbs, paprika, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll in onion mixture. 


                                               Place in a greased 13x9-in. baking dish. Drizzle with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350 for 50-60 minutes or until juices run clear.
                                                    Yield: 6 servings. 








                                            Originally published as Crunchy Baked Chicken in  Country
February/March 2008, p49                                                










